	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=12296&mid=105861884310877>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=12296&mid=105861884310877>Easy Kills</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=12296&mid=105861884310877#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Jul 19th 8:56 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=246501><span id= >Avanash</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>While trying for my shawl I found an easy way to hold the camp near the Skyshrine tower.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is easier with DMF or SoE...near the wyvern at the point just look over the edge of the cliff and you will see a single spawn on the left and 3 on the right.  It is much easier doing just the single but it takes forever to get the hair.  Just terror, fear and dark/snare then send pet and a DoT or 2.  You may have to re-fear but it is not always needed.  This keeps the mobs from even getting a spell off.  The tricky part is the 3 spawn.  From the cliff you will see one on the upper left, near middle and upper right.  Using the same spells start with the middle.  This shouldn't pull the others.  The upper right next the the upper left...just rinse and repeat til you have that stupid shawl... *sigh*</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
