	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=150996><span id= >The One and Only Rottenoak</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I can solo like 3 at a time as a 55 druid.&nbsp;&nbsp;Just focus on getting magic resist as high as possible and you will resist most, if not all, of their spells.  Mine is at 190 or so.  Of course, I try to root them and single them out for the kill rather than have 3 casting on me at once.  Also, there is a roaming bulark sp?, that you have to watch out for.  One siren is deep underwater and out from the coast.  I suggest single pulling that one first.  The other 3 (i think) are on the coast and its hard to single pull them.  Anyways, i've killed several and no hair has dropped.  I thought I got lucky and bought 2 &quot;locks of siren hair&quot; in the bazaar, but now I realize, thats not the right item.<br><br>Good luck,<br><br>Rottenoak</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
